Splunk Developer / Observability Engineer (Last 1 Year)

Developed and enhanced Java-based microservices integrated with Splunk for advanced observability and monitoring.

Implemented log ingestion using Splunk HTTP Event Collector (HEC), enabling real-time log streaming from microservices into Splunk.

Performed detailed log analysis using Splunk Processing Language (SPL) for root-cause identification, debugging, and performance tuning.

Built custom alerts, visualizations, and dashboards to monitor microservice health, performance metrics, API latency, error trends, and throughput.

Created Splunk monitoring dashboards to provide real-time visibility of distributed systems, improving operational awareness.

Improved system reliability through structured logging, correlation of distributed logs, and proactive alerting.

Collaborated with SRE/DevOps teams to enhance log quality, indexing strategy, and overall observability framework.
